# Button Semantic Colors

- Save / Confirm / Complete / Yes actions must be blue.
- Delete / Cancel / Remove / No actions must be red.
- Edit actions must use the `pencil` icon and appear before Delete actions.
- Delete actions must use the `trash` icon and appear after Edit actions.
- Action icon set is standardized app-wide and must stay consistent across all views.
- Ordering and color semantics are app-wide conventions, not per-screen preferences.
- Apply these semantics consistently in all new UI work and while touching existing screens.
- Prefer shared styling helpers when practical, but do not block shipping on full refactors.
- **Exception:** ``GuardianConfirmDanger`` uses a **red** primary for the proceed action and a **neutral** cancel — see ``guardian-confirm-dialogs`` (destructive confirm template only).

## Cursor (macOS)

- Use ``GuardianPointerPlainButtonStyle`` instead of `.buttonStyle(.plain)` on ``Button``, and append ``View/guardianPointerOnHover()`` after `.bordered` / `.borderedProminent` / `.borderless` (and on ``Menu`` chip triggers) so the pointer is a **pointing hand** over clickable controls. See ``GuardianButtonCursor.swift``.
